1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:06,610
The students had no interest in what the professor was saying, because the professor himself had no interest.

2
00:00:06,879 --> 00:00:09,889
He was bored with history, and it showed through.

3
00:00:10,240 --> 00:00:17,329
To activate others, to get them to be enthusiastic, you must first be enthusiastic yourself.

4
00:00:18,480 --> 00:00:22,849
Over the years I've tested this principle in hundreds of different situations.

5
00:00:23,038 --> 00:00:24,689
It always holds true.

6
00:00:25,038 --> 00:00:29,329
A man who lacks enthusiasm never develops it in another.

7
00:00:29,519 --> 00:00:34,610
But a person who is enthusiastic soon has enthusiastic followers.

8
00:00:35,278 --> 00:00:40,529
The enthusiastic salesman need never worry about unenthusiastic buyers.

9
00:00:40,718 --> 00:00:45,569
The enthusiastic teacher need never worry about disinterested students.

10
00:00:45,920 --> 00:00:51,088
The activated minister need never be distressed by a sleepy congregation.

11
00:00:53,038 --> 00:00:58,129
Enthusiasm can make things 1,100% better.

12
00:00:58,560 --> 00:01:07,250
Two years ago, employees in a business I'm acquainted with donated $94.35 to the Red Cross.

13
00:01:07,680 --> 00:01:18,449
This year, the same employees, with just about the same payroll, donated almost $1,100, an increase of 1,100%.

14
00:01:19,360 --> 00:01:26,529
The drive captain who collected only $94.35 was totally lacking in enthusiasm.

15
00:01:26,879 --> 00:01:31,170
He made remarks like, I suppose it's a worthwhile organization.

16
00:01:31,360 --> 00:01:33,889
I've never had any direct contact with it.

17
00:01:34,079 --> 00:01:37,810
It's a big organization and they collect a lot from the wealthy.

18
00:01:37,920 --> 00:01:41,329
So I suppose it's not too important if you contribute.

19
00:01:41,598 --> 00:01:44,209
If you can make a donation, see me.

20
00:01:44,560 --> 00:01:51,329
This fellow did nothing to inspire anyone to want to join the Red Cross and do it in a big way.

21
00:01:52,239 --> 00:01:54,930
This year's drive captain was a different sort.

22
00:01:55,040 --> 00:01:56,689
He had enthusiasm.

23
00:01:56,879 --> 00:02:03,170
He gave examples of case histories that showed how the Red Cross pitches in when disaster strikes.

24
00:02:03,439 --> 00:02:07,569
He showed how the Red Cross depends on donations from everyone.

25
00:02:07,839 --> 00:02:16,050
He asked the employees to be guided in giving by how much they would be willing to give their neighbor if disaster should strike him.

26
00:02:16,400 --> 00:02:19,249
He said, look what the Red Cross has done.

27
00:02:19,520 --> 00:02:21,650
Notice, he did not beg.

28
00:02:21,839 --> 00:02:26,530
He did not say, each of you is expected to donate XX dollars.

29
00:02:26,800 --> 00:02:31,569
All he did was to show enthusiasm about the importance of the Red Cross.

